'''Robert Eugene Brashers''' (March 13, 1958 – January 13, 1999) was an American [[serial killer]] and Rapist. In 2018 he was identified by [[CeCe Moore]], chief genetic genealogist at Parabon, via [[genetic genealogy]] as the murderer of Genevieve Zitricki in [[Greenville, South Carolina]] in 1990, the rapist of a 14 year old girl in 1997, and the killer of mother and daughter Sherri and Megan Scherer in [[Portageville, Missouri]] in 1998.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.greenvilleonline.com/story/news/crime/2018/10/05/greenville-cold-case-zitricki-murder-first-series-murders-across-three-states/1532153002/|title=Greenville cold case solved: Jenny Zitricki killed by serial killer Robert Brashers in 1990, police say|last1=Gross|first1=Daniel J.|last2=Lafleur|first2=Elizabeth|last3=Cavallaro|first3=Gabe|date=2018-10-05|work=Greenville News|access-date=2018-10-06|language=en}}</ref><ref>https://www.foxnews.com/us/1990s-cold-case-murders-in-south-carolina-missouri-solved-through-dna-breakthrough-police-say</ref> Brashers died in 1999 from a self-inflicted gunshot wound after he was approached by police officers in [[Kennett, Missouri]]. His body was exhumed in 2018 in order to collect a DNA sample and confirm a match to DNA evidence from the crime scenes.<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Robert Eugene Brashers|date=1999-01-15|work=Paragould Daily Press|access-date=|language=en|quote=Robert Eugene Brashers, 40, of Paragould died Wednesday, Jan. 13, 1999, in Dunklin Co., Mo. A graveside service will be at 10 a.m. Saturday at Shiloh Cemetery with Robert Jack officiating. Visitation will be from 6 to 9 this evening at Heath Funeral Home in Paragould.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dddnews.com/story/2556871.html|title=20 year old Portageville murder solved by DNA match|date=2018-10-06|work=Delta Dunklin Democrat|access-date=2018-10-06|language=en}}</ref>
